sql:
SELECT COUNT(record_id) AS total_records, 
       AVG(parking_duration) AS average_duration
FROM parking_records;

SELECT name, address
FROM parking_locations
WHERE capacity > 30;

SELECT record_id, vehicle_id, start_time, end_time, parking_duration, fee_paid, payment_method
FROM parking_records
ORDER BY parking_duration DESC;

SELECT COUNT(spot_id) 
FROM parking_spots 
WHERE status = 'occupied';

SELECT status, COUNT(spot_id) AS count
FROM parking_spots
GROUP BY status;

external_knowledge:
- 'Total parking records' refers to the number of times a vehicle type has been parked;
- 'Average parking duration' is the mean duration of parking sessions for each vehicle type;
- 'Total parking fee' is the sum of all fees paid for parking sessions of each vehicle type.

- "nestled in parking spots" refers to vehicles that are currently parked (i.e., `end_time` is `NULL`);
- "stewards who have checked in within the last month" refers to users who have logged in within the last 30 days;
- "rest" refers to the parking session, and "began their rest" refers to the start time of the parking session.

- "parking duration" refers to the time a vehicle is parked in minutes;
- "vehicles registered in California" means the vehicles have a `registered_state` value of 'CA';
- "more than half an hour" is equivalent to more than 30 minutes.

- 'Total parking duration' is the sum of all parking session durations for a specific spot type;
- 'Average fee paid' is the mean amount of parking fees paid for a specific vehicle type;
- 'Unknown' and '0' are used to handle missing data;
- 'Life' is used metaphorically to represent the context of the parking lot.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT v.owner_id) 
FROM vehicles v
JOIN parking_records pr ON v.vehicle_id = pr.vehicle_id;

external_knowledge:
- "Parking frequency" refers to the number of times a vehicle has been parked;
- "Usage of parking spots" refers to the number of times a parking spot has been occupied;
- "Distribution of vehicle types" refers to the count of vehicles of each type.

- "The golden state" is a nickname for California;
- A "long-duration parking session" is defined as a session lasting more than one hour;
- The query focuses on cars, not other types of vehicles.
